<task id="030" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>PCF manifest — add `searchIndexName` bound property (FR-PCF-01)</title>
    <phase>D: PCF SemanticSearchControl v1.1.74</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2-3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>018</dependencies>
    <blocks>031, 032, 033</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, react, typescript, frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies PCF manifest (the maker-facing contract for downstream PCF tasks); carries ADR-006 / ADR-011 / ADR-012 / ADR-021 / ADR-022 obligations; manifest typing regeneration affects 031 + 032 consumers.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Manifest is the contract for downstream PCF code consumers (tasks 031, 032). Must complete first.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add a new bound property `searchIndexName` (SingleLine.Text, bound, not required) to `ControlManifest.Input.xml` representing the scope record's `sprk_searchindexname` field. Regenerate manifest types if needed so downstream code can read the property via `context.parameters.searchIndexName.raw`. Verify the PCF rebuilds and the maker can wire the field on a form (FR-PCF-01).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    PCF developer with deep familiarity with `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/`, ADR-006 (PCF over webresources), ADR-011 (PCF conventions), ADR-012 (shared lib), ADR-021 (Fluent v9 + dark mode + tokens), ADR-022 (PCF stays React 16). Bound-property authoring is routine in PCF; mirror the shape of existing bound properties in the manifest.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ControlManifest.Input.xml` declares a new bound `searchIndexName` property; PCF rebuilds via `npm run build` (validation only — production build is in task 035); maker portal lists the new property as bindable on a form. Downstream code (tasks 031 + 032) can read it via the regenerated manifest types.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The multi-container-multi-index project routes search requests to the correct Azure AI Search index per record (FR-PCF-02 + FR-PCF-03 downstream). The PCF needs a manifest-level bound property so makers can wire the scope record's `sprk_searchindexname` field on the form. This task adds the manifest declaration only — the consumer code (API service + NavigationService) lands in tasks 031 + 032.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/ControlManifest.Input.xml</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/index.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-PCF-01">PCF manifest MUST add a new bound property `searchIndexName` (SingleLine.Text, bound) representing the scope record's `sprk_searchindexname` field.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">PCF over web-resources — manifest authoring stays in `ControlManifest.Input.xml`; no parallel webresource wiring.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-011">PCF conventions — follow the existing bound-property attribute set used by the other properties in this manifest (do not introduce a different shape).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">PCF code consuming the shared lib remains untouched here — this task is manifest-only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 + tokens.* only when this property's value renders. Manifest itself has no styling; downstream UI must comply.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">PCF stays React 16-safe. Manifest additions never introduce React 18-only APIs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No version bump in this task — version stays at 1.1.73 until task 033. This task is additive manifest only.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006-pcf-over-webresources.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-011-pcf-conventions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-ui-component-library.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-ui-v9.md</file>
