      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Bound property declaration" location="src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/ControlManifest.Input.xml">
        Existing bound properties in this manifest define the canonical attribute set (name, display-name-key, description-key, of-type, usage="bound", required="false"). Mirror that exact shape.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `ControlManifest.Input.xml` to identify the existing bound-property attribute set (display-name-key, description-key, of-type, usage, required). Note any `resx`/localization keys that mirror the pattern.</step>
    <step order="2">Add a new `&lt;property&gt;` element: `name="searchIndexName"`, `display-name-key="searchIndexName_Display_Key"`, `description-key="searchIndexName_Desc_Key"`, `of-type="SingleLine.Text"`, `usage="bound"`, `required="false"`. Place near other bound properties for readability.</step>
    <step order="3">If localization resx files exist for this control, add the matching display-name + description entries. If no resx exists (inline display names used), use the inline `display-name-key` attribute directly per the existing convention.</step>
    <step order="4">Run `npm run build` (NOT prod — that's task 035) in `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/` to regenerate manifest types and verify TypeScript compiles. Confirm `context.parameters.searchIndexName` is type-safe in downstream code (smoke check `index.ts` if needed).</step>
    <step order="5">Verify the PCF still compiles cleanly with no new TypeScript or PCF tooling warnings. Capture the build summary in `projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/030-pcf-manifest-build.md`.</step>
    <step order="6">Run code-review + adr-check skills at Step 9.5 (FULL rigor requirement). Update `TASK-INDEX.md` status: 🔲 → ✅. Update `current-task.md` to reflect completion and advance to next task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read ControlManifest.Input.xml and index.ts</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Add the new bound property declaration</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run `npm run build` to regenerate manifest types</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/ControlManifest.Input.xml (new bound property)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/030-pcf-manifest-build.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-PCF-01: `ControlManifest.Input.xml` contains a `&lt;property name="searchIndexName" of-type="SingleLine.Text" usage="bound" required="false" /&gt;` declaration with the existing attribute set.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PCF rebuild via `npm run build` succeeds with no TypeScript errors; regenerated manifest types expose `context.parameters.searchIndexName`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Maker portal lists `searchIndexName` as a bindable property on the control (UI test below).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="PCF manifest property visible to maker">
      <description>Verify the new bound property is discoverable in the maker portal control configuration.</description>
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=control</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open maker portal and navigate to a model-driven form that hosts SemanticSearchControl.</step>
        <step>Click the SemanticSearchControl on the form to open the control configuration pane.</step>
        <step>Inspect the list of bindable properties.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Property `searchIndexName` is listed alongside existing bound properties; maker can map it to a Dataverse column.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    This task is manifest-only. Consumer code (the actual request body + navigateTo envelope additions) lands in tasks 031 + 032. The version bump to 1.1.74 lands in task 033 — do NOT bump here.

    If the manifest uses inline `display-name-key` values rather than resx (check the existing properties first), follow that convention for the new property. Localization is not in scope for this task.
  </notes>

